## Using with a Datadog test-drive

A test-drive is an ephemeral, isolated environment that lives behind the Datadog
staging API. It is selected per request by sending a `test-drive-<name>: 1`
header while the provider is pointed at the staging API URL. Use the generic
`default_headers` attribute (or the `DD_HTTP_CLIENT_DEFAULT_HEADERS` environment
variable) to attach that header to every request.

Using the provider configuration:

```hcl
provider "datadog" {
  api_url = "https://api.datad0g.com"

  default_headers = {
    "test-drive-<name>" = "1"
  }
}
```

Or entirely through environment variables (no provider block changes needed):

```shell
export DD_HOST="https://api.datad0g.com"
export DD_HTTP_CLIENT_DEFAULT_HEADERS='{"test-drive-<name>":"1"}'
export DD_API_KEY="<staging-api-key>"
export DD_APP_KEY="<staging-app-key>"
```

Replace `<name>` with the test-drive name. If the staging credentials cannot be
validated at startup, set `validate = false` on the provider (or `DD_VALIDATE=false`).

